
WIFI:
=====

/etc/network/interfaces
/etc/wpa.conf

WIFI-Scan:
   https://rasspberrypi.wordpress.com/2012/09/09/wifi-tools-for-raspberry-pi/



/etc/modprobe.d/8192cu.conf
    options 8192cu rtw_power_mgnt=0 rtw_enusbss=0
chown root.root
chmod 644 8192cu.conf


NFS:
====

local: /etc/fstab
server: /etc/exports



Misc
====



sudo apt-get install vim  

# ~/.vimrc
syntax on
set number
set expandtab


Libs:
=====


wiringPi
--------

http://raspi.tv/how-to-install-wiringpi2-for-python-on-the-raspberry-pi

sudo apt-get install python-dev python-pip
sudo pip install wiringpi2



i2c smb
-------

https://learn.adafruit.com/adafruits-raspberry-pi-lesson-4-gpio-setup/configuring-i2c

sudo apt-get install python-smbus
sudo apt-get install i2c-tools

sudo raspi-config
  --> Advanced Options
      --> Enable SPI
      --> Enable I2C


/etc/modules    add lines:
i2c-bcm2708 
i2c-dev

/root/config.txt add lines:

dtparam=i2c1=on
dtparam=i2c_arm=on


reboot

Test:
sudo i2cdetect -y 1




1-wire (DS1820)
---------------

/boot/config.txt:
   dtoverlay=w1-gpio,gpiopin=4
/etc/modules:
   w1-gpio pullup=1
   w1-therm


DHT22_AM2302:
-------------

mkdir dhtreader
cd dhtreader/
wget http://www.airspayce.com/mikem/bcm2835/bcm2835-1.45.tar.gz 
tar xvf bcm2835-1.45.tar.gz 
cd bcm2835-1.45/
./configure 
make
sudo make check
sudo make install


git clone https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit_Python_DHT.git 
cd Adafruit_Python_DHT
sudo apt-get install build-essential python-dev  
sudo python setup.py build
sudo python setup.py install 


Kamera:
-------
https://github.com/jacksonliam/mjpg-streamer
sudo aptitude install cmake libx11-dev libjpeg62-dev
http://www.forum-raspberrypi.de/Thread-tutorial-rasperry-pi-als-hd-mjpeg-netzwerkkamera-zoneminder



GIT
===

https://help.github.com/articles/generating-ssh-keys/#platform-linux


sudo apt-get install git
git clone https://github.com/thomaspfeiffer-git/raspberry

create file "ci" (shell script for checkin)

copy .git/config

    git config --global user.email "thomas.pfeiffer@smtp.at"
    git config --global user.name "thomaspfeiffer-git"

    https://help.github.com/articles/changing-a-remote-s-url/


RRDTool
=======

sudo apt-get install rrdtool python-rrdtool








